alllllll i want for christmas is for all my friends to sweat with me for LIVMAS🎅🏻🎄🥳 team!! extending early bird sign ups for one more day because the sun is shining and it’s the first day of december and i want us to set the month up RIGHT! 

WHAT’S LIVMAS YOU ASK? LIVMAS is a 12 day fitness challenge: 12 days of workouts, with 12 days of amazing giveaways, with $25 from every sign up going to the food banks of canada!!!❤️

in addition to 1 life coaching session with @fabigord from @dolifework , a nutrition workshop with holistic nutritionist, @stephrobinnson , a cooking class with chef and author, @dialaskitchen from dialas kitchen, and a yoga class with @jes_mindovermess ✨🫶🏼

all workouts are done with minimal equipment and can be done anywhere - at home, at the gym, outside! classes range from 30 to 45 minutes, they run AM and PM, and all participants have the option to join LIVE or do class at their own time through the LIVMAS library afterwards! 🌟new this year, i’m also introducing an IRL pop up for my local bbs to join!

okay so restaurants and activities in the last post… now the ones you all asked for… bachelorette/birthday/party vibes🥳💍 literally everything in vegas is over the top in every way so if you’re looking to celebrate - sky is the limit lololol and i’m happy to share from my chaotic past trips there😂🎉

OUT: you can find every dj in vegas (especially in the summer months) so i’d say go where you prefer who’s playing! this goes for night time too! encore beach club + wet republic are probably top 2 pool party spots for me🛟hakkassan, xs, wynn, for night time! omnia is absolutely insane, their bottle service literally comes from the ceiling! bachelorette fun forsure🎀

for fun dinner out: carbone specifically the one in vegas is a must and the food is🙌🏼, beauty and essex - dinner + fun + foood is so good! kassi beach club (a restaurant) is outdoor tulum vibes chic + the food was amazing! also again delilah and catch from my last post are favs🫶🏼

chandelier bar at the cosmo is sparkly and aesthetic and cute to go for a drink before dinner, also sky bar at the waldorf for a before or after bevy🍸

party BRUNCH is another fav activity🥂 lavo, catch, beauty and essex, then classic brunch:
saddelles, tableau, herringbone + eggslut🍳

OTHER FUN! sugar factory - over the top desserts + cocktails but they moved locations and i haven’t been since then! used to be a patio on the strip but it’s a fun dessert celebration photo opp! fat tuesdays are everywhere for fun blended cocktails on the go! milk bar coookies + icecream are just BEST🍭🍦🍬

and then truly had a time at dry bar if you’re going go before going out and have a couple cocktails/mocktails while you get GLAM✨

last i will say there are sooo many good MOCKTAILS and zero proof alcohol drinks everywhere now which we love love love to see🫶🏼

alright, save this! HAVE FUN. BE SAFE💋🎲🍸🎰✨

the one ya been asking for: TULUM RECCOS💖🌴 i really love sharing all my favourite places to eat + drink and tulum is a personal FAV! i’ve been a few times and it’s up there with top places to lay by a beach while also having lots of options to go out🍸 last time i was here was in april with my girlfriends for my birthday - so a very different trip, and both times it was a goood time so here are some of my favs🫶🏼 save for your tulum TRIP!

to dine🍴🥂
hartwood: fav restaurant in tulum! the food is amazing, the vibe is perfect and the service was lovely! everything is so good💖

kitchen table: also really good food - the patio is gorgeous, food + vibe were a 10! the ceviche was chefs kiss!

casa banana - argentinian restaurant - the cocktails were dreamy and so was the food! 

gitano - mexican food! the food is goood, and the drinks are good but i think the vibe is the what gets people here! it’s big and it becomes a bar/late night spot after dinner and is fun! aesthetic, good dj!

casa jaguar - vibey very tulum vibes, thursdays are the big night here: it’s also a restaurant and then becomes a party later into the night! a classic tulum spot!

rosanegra - honestly i would say do it once! it’s a hoot! they have sparklers on the hour every hour on the weekend + dj! it’s one of those over the top restaurants and very fun if you’re celebrating or want to have a night! food is good - drinks are good - vibe is like a party dinner so it’s a good time. again - sparklers every hour🥳🧨

kintoh - SO, this is the most stunning restaurant! whether you’re in a nest or at a regular table the experience of just being there is amazing. it’s located at azulik and it IS gorgeous. i will say the food isn’t amazing and its very overpriced (even for tulum which is already an expensive destination) with small portions. that’s just my opinion, i’d say 1000% go to the roof for cocktails + sunset which they do every night with a dj from 5-8pm - it is perfect!

for day club/beach parties: tantra, taboo + bagatelle! rosanegra also has a day club that’s a littttle more chill but still has a dj! went to tantra for my 30th with my gfs and we had a TIME🎉

bb girl booked a one way ticket to bali✈️🌴✨💖 and my goodness it took so long to get here i might never do the trip back🙃 2 full days, 3 flights and 24 hours in the sky, but we made it!

first, i am celebrating a milestone: happy one year of therapy to me🎈 i can’t believe i started therapy a year ago! there were forsure a few lows last year that pushed me to start. i made a pact with myself to finally use this tool and go every week, and i’m really proud of myself for sticking with it🤍 therapy is cool!!!🧠 (side note: it takes some time to find a therapist that you connect with! don’t get discouraged!! i have a list in my highlights that i compiled for resources/a place to start🌱🫶🏼)

anyways.. i’m having a little eat pray love moment! not my usual escape to cities where i’m spending too much and drinking too much.. but a solo trip (actually solo lol - first time!!) that is all things wellness and just for me❤️‍🩹

i’m spending the first week exploring🌎 and then i’m doing my yoga teachers certification which is something i’ve wanted to do since i was 15!!🧘🏽‍♀️✨ and then we’ll see what’s next!! i was originally supposed to be going to bali in february with a company for work that ended up not aligning with me and my values. something just didn’t feel right about it! honestly i think i only engaged in the idea because i wanted to go to bali, not the job itself, so i ended up turning it down. i did some research, put my self on a waitlist for this amazing retreat and when i got the call - i felt it was a sign to GO✨ between the YTT + being in bali, we are checking 2 big things off the bucket list ✅🎉 i’ve never been to this side of the world so i’m excited to explore + learn, and i’m extra excited to really dive into this next chapter of self love + growth🤸🏽‍♀️🥳 let’s fkn go!
